cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.DS

This paper deals with nonmonotonic reasoning and logic programming, which are topics that are commonly studied in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO) communities. The paper also discusses the embedding of the logic of grounded knowledge (GK) into general logic programming (cs.PL), and the use of disjunctive ASP solvers (cs.CL) to compute the extension/expansion semantics of various nonmonotonic logics. Finally, the paper involves computational complexity analysis (cs.DS) of the translation from GK to disjunctive logic programming.
